@Node "DropAndCall()" "mebbsarexx.library/DropAndCall"

 NAME
 DropAndCall -- Hang up and call phone number. (v1.7)

 SYNOPSIS
 DropAndCall DoorName , LineNumber , PhoneNumber

 FUNCTION
 Hangs up on user and calls telephone number.

 INPUTS
 DoorName - Name of door or utility.
 LineNumber - Number of door which launches the function.
 PhoneNumber - Telephone number to call. Must include area code and
               other pertinent info required to make the call.

 RESULT
 Successful connect returns 'Connect' otherwise returns 'Fail'.

 EXAMPLE

 NOTES
 Door only.

 BUGS

 SEE ALSO


@EndNode

@Node "EditFile()" "mebbsarexx.library/EditFile"

 NAME
 EditFile -- Allows editing of a file.

 SYNOPSIS
 EditFile DoorName , LineNumber ,FileName , MaxLines

 FUNCTION
 Calls the MEBBSNet line editor and loads FileName or creates FileName
 if not found.  Maximum number of lines editable governed by the value
 of MaxLines. Strips all ctl-M characters and adds a newline to
 the beginning of the file.

 INPUTS
 DoorName - Name of door.
 LineNumber - Number of line launching the door.
 FileName - File name which will be transferred. This must include the
            full path to the file.
 MaxLines - Maximum number of lines which will be allowed for entry.

 RESULT
 Success returns string 'Done'.

 EXAMPLE

 NOTES
 Door only.

 BUGS

 SEE ALSO

@EndNode

@Node "Exit_Door()" "mebbsarexx.library/Exit_Door"

 NAME
 Exit_Door -- Signal door function processing termination.

 SYNOPSIS
 Exit_Door DoorName , LineNumber 

 FUNCTION
 Signals MEBBSNet that door processing has ended.

 INPUTS
 DoorName - Name of door or utility.
 LineNumber - Number of door which launches the function.

 RESULT
 Returns 'Exit ARexx door.' This function MUST be called before your
 ARexx script terminates. There is one exception to this requirement.
 If your script calls @{"HangUp" Link "MEBBSARexx.GUIDE/HangUp()"}, MEBBSNet will exit the door as well.
 DO NOT call Exit_Door if you call @{"HangUp" Link "MEBBSARexx.GUIDE/HangUp()"}. This is only applicable
 to ARexx scripts which are started by the BBS (doors).  DO NOT call
 this function if the ARexx script is a stand-alone utility.

 EXAMPLE

 NOTES
 Door only.

 BUGS

 SEE ALSO


@EndNode

